metadata.name: Mooncakes: Happy Mid Autumn Festival 2022 #834
metadata.description:
To celebrate the Moon Festival with Mooncakes, we have created a quest to introduce everyone to fxhash. As part of that quest on mooncakes.fun, users are encouraged to mint this generative token.

This is a layered image composition using the Mooncakes site images on a 1920x1080 canvas. The image elements are randomly assigned position, scale, tint, and blur according to a ruleset which generates a Mid Autumn Festival scene made up of: Moon, Clouds, Stars, Lanterns, and Lotuses.

Special filters, shapes and colors are included as rare features, as well as a couple of surprises.

metadata.name: Teleport Loopr #98
metadata.description:
Video-art loop randomly generated by a p5.js code ~

_ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _

Assuming that teleports would rearrange the experience of time, how would time feel like if you were trapped into teleport loops?

This is a project about time

, space

, displacement

, deterritorialization

, abstraction

, reterritorialization

, inversion?

A dream looper, a teleport machine.

_ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _

There were 30 .mp4 files available to be randomly chosen.

All videos take part on my audiovisual research and were recorded between 2016 and 2021 in Brasil, Chile and Canary Islands. They're all short and looped in this project, just like moving photos.

Videos per iteration could be:

[3], [4] or [5]

Color inversion effect could have been applied to:

[one video], [none (rare)] or [variable (super rare)]

_ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _

by Filipe Britto

@fitipeArt (twitter)

@fitipe (ig)

metadata.name: adrift #106
metadata.description:
Take your entire life, full as it is with the vastness of your lived experiences – and shape it into your cupped hands. Cherish this mesmerising world of yours as you would a ripe summer fruit, and behold at a glance its delicate yet dynamic balance — one change here or there, no matter how microscopic, affects the entire course of your world. 

How will you receive this world – its situations that overwhelm, its sights that awe, the catastrophes, the serenity, its steadfast commitment to the present? Will you look upon all of us here, adrift and fragile together, with love?


Adrift is a project that reminds us to make peace with our world – with all worlds – by stepping back to make space for an all-encompassing perspective.


------------


Created by Jacek Markusiewicz @jMarkusiewicz
Creative collaboration with Tender @tender_art

Click on the image for resolution options and to save a .png file. Saving higher resolutions may not work in some browsers; in these cases, right-click-save the image. All drawing and geometric methods are written by mrkswcz using javascript, except for the following:

The pseudorandom terrain generation uses Hydraulic-Erosion by Sebastian Lague, inspired by "Reconnaissance" by TENDER x Nat Sarkissian (MIT License).

For finding paths that simulate connections in terrain and potential locations of cities, a C# script was adapted from the article "Pathfinding Algorithms in C#" by Kristian Ekman published in Code Project licensed under The Code Project Open License (CPOL). The code was translated to javascript and simplified for performance.

Many pseudorandom effects are achieved with perlin-simplex by David Guttman and seedrandom by David Bau (both MIT Licenses)

For more information, please see the bundle.js.LICENSE.txt file included in the package.

The "heat death" event is a small tribute to lunarean's fxhash project. The code that generates the disintegration effect interprets a fragment of lunarean's code. Further contributions are its adaptation for 3d transformations and its recursive character that modifies certain parameters over time.

The project uses CPU for calculations and rendering – generating the image requires up to 500MB of free RAM. Testing was performed across browsers and devices, but please make sure it works on your device before minting. Note that there are minor colour-intensity differences between different browsers.

metadata.name: Melody #7
metadata.description:
Each output is generated by layering Blender renders.

The iterations are best viewed in Live Mode.

'Melody' explores color, space and geometry... with a touch of optical illusion thrown in!

It is called 'Melody' because each image resembles notes on a sheet of music.

In live mode:
Click/tap the image to make a "Download image" button appear. Click this button to download a 1800x2400px PNG.

metadata.name: Finestre #440
metadata.description:
"Finestre" means windows or apertures in Italian. This generative art project was inspired by the appreciation of collected memories, windows in time to our past experiences and loved ones. Using basic geometry such as rectangles, squares, circles, ellipses, triangles with random compositions and many possible color palettes, Finestre presents our impression of portals to the Universes of collected memories through abstract still code-based outputs.

Finestre is a collaboration generative art project between generative artists Gonz0x and Schizzo.

Finestre has some fun interactive features which allows collectors to view the work in different configurations. For example, collectors can isolate the deconstructed background layers, isolate the main constructed layer, add Grain and also enter a Free Play mode which allows for the option to draw background and foreground layers, stacking infinitely. You can Save off a render as a .png.

Press "C" for Constructed Mode (Isolate Foreground)
Press "D" for Deconstructed Mode (Isolate Background)
Press "R" to reset to Default = C & D
Press "G" to add grain texture with each press
Press "S" saves render
 
Press "F" to toggle Free Play mode
In Free Play, Press "Q" repeatedly to add Deconstructed layers
In Free Play, Press "W" repeatedly to add Constructed layers

metadata.name: Solace #114
metadata.description:
Solace is an algorithm that generates artworks of sand dunes. It draws hundreds of thousands of tiny points according to a probability distribution calculated from the positions of the dunes.

The logic to divide the dunes into light and dark sides is simple, but produces some interesting chaotic behaviour. These are details that weren't hard-coded but emerge organically, such as the patterns on the spines of the dunes or the stripes around their bases.

Please note that the algorithm can take some time to run, especially when the number of dunes is high.

Created by lunarean.

metadata.name: Nothing Remains #60
metadata.description:
The only time I ever received corporal punishment – something that was still legal in schools during the 1970s – was in Double Maths with Mrs Robinson. The log book spread out before me seemed less appealing than talking with my friends at the back of the classroom, and so it was I found myself, palm outstretched, feeling the whack of Mrs. Robinson's ruler, ten times over. "Math sucks." Or so I thought.

Back then I knew nothing of the beauty that I would later see in Mathematics – something which became apparent as I taught myself to code, especially using Processing.

This work – based on code I've been playing around with since 2009 – is my small homage to that beauty. Originally based on Ulam spirals, I've then played around with that starting formula to create an infinite numbers of patterns using square roots, cosines and modulus. If only they had shown me these possibilities when I was younger I may have avoided the dreaded ruler of Mrs. Robinson.

metadata.name: FxPlanet #125
metadata.description:
🟢〰Storyline〰🟢

Once upon a time, a God had a little daughter. The daughter liked to explore the planets on his father's cosmos. Suddenly the daughter got sick and died like a collapsing star. God gets alone, angry, depressed and finally mad. He turned all the universe to ash and mixed the ash of her daughter's soul with it to make her alive, But he failed. In the end, he decided to destroy himself to make a New cosmos of all generative planets from ash of himself and his daughter's soul to one more time in the eternity they can be with each other in a heart of a planet. If you listen carefully to the planets, you may hear them calling each other.

⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛

🔴〰Rarity〰🔴

This collection is a 3D generative interactive artwork (Made with Unity Game Engine) that contains of 9999+1 planets (1 shared source of light and 9999 pieces of souls) from billions of variation. You can see more random variations from fxhash page.
◼ The beauty and complexity of the Planet's surface is important, But what is going on inside?
Each planet has three grades of volume (High, Medium, Low) that show you what resources exist on the planets (Common, Rare, Legendary).
Some resources are so valuable and infrequent.
◼ For Example: It's possible to get Oxygen (Legendary Resource) on Low volume slot, but it's infrequent if you get it on High volume slot.
◼ Checkout Material rarity list on webpage.

📎 Webpage address: HashProtocol.tez.page

⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛

🔵〰Social〰🔵

◼ Participant in events or get achievements to win some prizes.
So it's significant to see you on the discord server. Checkout rarity table, achievements rewards, … on the webpage.
📎 Webpage address: HashProtocol.tez.page

⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛

🟠〰Interact〰🟠

◼ You can rotate around of planets by “WASD” keys on the keyboard or arrow keys.
◼ Zoom In by “E” key and Zoom Out by “Q”.
◼ Full HD texture by Key “1”.
◼ 4k texture by Key “2”.
◼ 8k texture by Key “3”.

metadata.name: FxPlanet #115
metadata.description:
🟢〰Storyline〰🟢

Once upon a time, a God had a little daughter. The daughter liked to explore the planets on his father's cosmos. Suddenly the daughter got sick and died like a collapsing star. God gets alone, angry, depressed and finally mad. He turned all the universe to ash and mixed the ash of her daughter's soul with it to make her alive, But he failed. In the end, he decided to destroy himself to make a New cosmos of all generative planets from ash of himself and his daughter's soul to one more time in the eternity they can be with each other in a heart of a planet. If you listen carefully to the planets, you may hear them calling each other.

⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛

🔴〰Rarity〰🔴

This collection is a 3D generative interactive artwork (Made with Unity Game Engine) that contains of 9999+1 planets (1 shared source of light and 9999 pieces of souls) from billions of variation. You can see more random variations from fxhash page.
◼ The beauty and complexity of the Planet's surface is important, But what is going on inside?
Each planet has three grades of volume (High, Medium, Low) that show you what resources exist on the planets (Common, Rare, Legendary).
Some resources are so valuable and infrequent.
◼ For Example: It's possible to get Oxygen (Legendary Resource) on Low volume slot, but it's infrequent if you get it on High volume slot.
◼ Checkout Material rarity list on webpage.

📎 Webpage address: HashProtocol.tez.page

⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛

🔵〰Social〰🔵

◼ Participant in events or get achievements to win some prizes.
So it's significant to see you on the discord server. Checkout rarity table, achievements rewards, … on the webpage.
📎 Webpage address: HashProtocol.tez.page

⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛

🟠〰Interact〰🟠

◼ You can rotate around of planets by “WASD” keys on the keyboard or arrow keys.
◼ Zoom In by “E” key and Zoom Out by “Q”.
◼ Full HD texture by Key “1”.
◼ 4k texture by Key “2”.
◼ 8k texture by Key “3”.
